/**
\page org_mitk_views_docker_volcano Volcano Analysis View

\imageMacro{VolcanoIcon.svg,"Icon of the Volcano Analysis View",2.00}

\tableofcontents

\section org_mitk_views_docker_volcano_intro Introduction

The Volcano Analysis View provides a Docker-based differential expression analysis tool for mass spectrometry imaging data. This plugin performs region-based statistical comparisons between two groups defined in a segmentation mask, generating volcano plots and identifying significantly different m/z features.

\section org_mitk_views_docker_volcano_prereqs Prerequisites

- Docker must be installed and running on your system
- The Docker image ghcr.io/cemos-mannheim/volcanodocker:main will be automatically pulled when needed
- A spectrum image must be loaded in M2aia
- A segmentation mask with at least two labeled regions must be created

\section org_mitk_views_docker_volcano_usage Usage

1. Select a spectrum image from the Data Manager
2. (Optional) Select centroid lists to analyze specific m/z values
3. Select a segmentation mask that defines the groups to compare
4. Choose Group 1 and Group 2 from the dropdown menus (based on mask labels)
5. Configure statistical parameters:
   - Alpha: Significance threshold (default: 0.05)
   - Log2 FC Threshold: Minimum fold change (default: 1.0)
   - Min Regions: Minimum regions to avoid bootstrapping (default: 3)
   - Bootstrap N: Number of bootstrap replicates (default: 3)
   - Bootstrap Pixels: Pixels per bootstrap replicate (default: 50)
6. Click "Run Volcano Analysis"

The plugin will:
- Extract ion images from centroids or current display
- Compare intensity distributions between the two groups
- Perform statistical testing (with bootstrapping if needed)
- Generate volcano plot results showing differential features

\section org_mitk_views_docker_volcano_params Parameters

- **Alpha**: Statistical significance threshold (p-value cutoff)
- **Log2 FC Threshold**: Minimum log2 fold change to be considered biologically significant
- **Min Regions**: If fewer regions than this exist, bootstrapping is used
- **Bootstrap N**: Number of bootstrap replicates for small sample sizes
- **Bootstrap Pixels**: Number of pixels sampled per bootstrap replicate

\section org_mitk_views_docker_volcano_output Output

The analysis generates CSV files with volcano plot data including:
- m/z values
- Log2 fold changes
- P-values
- Significance indicators

Results are saved to the output directory and can be visualized externally.

*/
